                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00 Revolutions/40: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-27T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 27, 1931—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Your 75, April 27, 11 a.m. The Naval Attachè of the American Legation in
                    Honduras should not be employed to obtain military information for the
                    Government or take part in Honduran internal political affairs.</p>
                <p>The participation in military operations of an airplane employed in purely
                    commercial pursuits by an American company in Honduras is viewed with much
                    apprehension by the Department of State.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
